meanings.definition: (有機化学) シアメル酸塩

etymology.value: Derived from cyamelic acid + -id (suffix used to denote a salt).

usage_notes.explanation: This term is highly specialized and primarily used within the field of organic chemistry.

readability_explanation.text: This term is highly technical and specific to organic chemistry. It is unlikely to be encountered outside of specialized scientific literature or discussions. Understanding requires knowledge of chemical nomenclature and organic acids.
